  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Dhanya M versus State of Kerala & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_7_354_363','2025INSC809'); ><font size='4'> <strong>DHANYA M<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF KERALA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 354</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 809</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002772025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KAROL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, MANMOHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the preventive detention of the detenu is in accordance with law. Headnotes&dagger; Kerala Anti-Social Activities (Prevention) Act, 2007 &ndash; ss.3, 2(j), (o) &ndash; Order of detention u/s.3(1), if sustainable: Held: No &ndash; s.2(j) states that a person who is covered by the Act &ndash; In the present case, the facts and circumstances do not fall under the category of a public order situation &ndash; The detention order does not state any reason as to how the actions of the detenu were against the public order of the State &ndash; Given the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-06-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2897/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_7_354_363','2025INSC809','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outli